  <steps>
    <step order="1">Run `Glob '.claude/adr/ADR-*.md'` (sorted) — identify the highest existing ADR ordinal. Pick the next available number (call it `NNN` for this POML).</step>
    <step order="2">Read `.claude/adr/ADR-033-streaming-chat-tool-side-channel.md` and `.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md` to confirm ADR style + section conventions used in this repo's concise form.</step>
    <step order="3">Read 114R/114a/114b POMLs (now ✅ in TASK-INDEX) to confirm the as-built behavior the ADR documents.</step>
    <step order="4">Author `.claude/adr/ADR-NNN-multinode-output-composition.md` (concise, ≤80 lines): Status, Context (5-coordination-point frailty), Decision (section-name-keyed routing via `NodeType.DeliverComposite`), MUSTs / MUST NOTs, references to 114R/114a/114b + FR-52/53/54.</step>
    <step order="5">Author `docs/adr/ADR-NNN-multinode-output-composition.md` (full): Status, Context, Decision, Alternatives Considered (e.g., per-Action streaming with no Output node; schema-position keyed with stricter naming), Consequences (positive: coordination 5→2; negative: migration cost per playbook), Migration Path (per-playbook incremental; pilot is `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` via FR-58 / task 118R), When NOT to use (chat sibling stays single-action — no composition benefit when only one output destination).</step>
    <step order="6">Update `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` — add the new ADR to the index with one-line summary.</step>
    <step order="7">Add a `.claude/CHANGELOG.md` entry — dated, naming the project (`chat-routing-redesign-r1`), the new ADR number, and one-sentence summary.</step>
    <step order="8">Validate cross-references render correctly (no broken links); validate markdown lints clean.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 114c → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 118R (the migration pilot consumer of this ADR).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Glob">Enumerate existing ADR ordinals</tool>
    <tool name="Read">ADR style exemplars, 114R/114a/114b POMLs</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Two new ADR markdown files</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">.claude/adr/INDEX.md, .claude/CHANGELOG.md</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
