  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Concise ADR exists at `.claude/adr/ADR-NNN-multinode-output-composition.md` (≤80 lines; MUST/MUST NOT form).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Full ADR exists at `docs/adr/ADR-NNN-multinode-output-composition.md` with Alternatives Considered + Migration Path + When NOT to use sections.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ADR captures the 5→2 coordination-point reduction rationale and the schema-on-action + schema-aware widget frailty being replaced.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Migration path explicitly names FR-58 / task 118R as the pilot (`summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">"When NOT to use composite" guidance includes the chat sibling single-action case.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`.claude/adr/INDEX.md` lists the new ADR; `.claude/CHANGELOG.md` entry added (dated, project-attributed).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ADR number is NOT hardcoded — implementer picked next available via Glob at execution time.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    **MAIN-SESSION-ONLY task.** Per CLAUDE.md §3 sub-agent write boundary, sub-agents launched via the Agent tool CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths (skills, patterns, constraints, catalogs, agents, settings, ADRs, INDEX, CHANGELOG). This POML's body explicitly references `.claude/adr/` and `.claude/CHANGELOG.md` writes — therefore the task-execute skill MUST route this task to the MAIN session and NOT delegate to a sub-agent. If a sub-agent attempts this and reports "Edit denied on `.claude/...`" — that is the boundary working correctly; escalate to main session immediately. Wave 5-C documentation capstone; blocks 118R (migration pilot).
  </notes>

